Preamble
--------

This program asks the user to input up to 100 integers to then find the sum of
it all either via recursion or iteration. The callstack information is displayed
before the resulting sum is shown.


Compilation Command
-------------------

  gcc -o a2 a2.c a2loop.c a2Stack.c


Launching and Operating Instructions
------------------------------------

Run the program with the following command:

  ./a2

Input up to 100 integers, each integer followed by a newline (return key). Enter
either the 'r' character or 'i' character to find the sum of the entered
integers using recursive or iterative summation, respectively.


Files Included
--------------

Root Dir
 |-> a2.c
 |-> a2loop.c
 |-> a2Stack.c
 |-> a2Defs.h
 |-> README
